data.value: The 2018 Toyota Corolla is a compact sedan renowned for its reliability and efficiency. Under the hood, it houses a 1.8-liter 4-cylinder engine producing 132 horsepower, delivering a balanced mix of power and fuel economy. Paired with a continuously variable transmission (CVT), the Corolla offers smooth acceleration and excellent fuel efficiency, with an EPA-estimated 28 mpg in the city and 36 mpg on the highway. Its exterior features 16-inch steel wheels and LED headlights, adding to its modern and stylish appearance. Inside, the Corolla offers a comfortable cabin with cloth-trimmed seats and a user-friendly infotainment system with a 6.1-inch touchscreen display. Advanced safety features, including Toyota Safety Sense-P (TSS-P) with automatic emergency braking and lane departure warning, ensure peace of mind for both the driver and passengers. With a mileage of 35,000 miles and a price of $15,000, the 2018 Toyota Corolla presents an excellent value proposition, combining affordability, reliability, and advanced safety features in one attractive package.
